Comment: This was a lot of fun! I learned so much about set() and finding common elements through this task—thank you for the great example. I have a bit of a fever for crafting one-liners, even when they don't always make sense. Here’s the solution I came up with:

print(*sorted(set(map(int,input().split()))&set(map(int,input().split())))or["none"])

Goal
* Please add a space between "order." and "If".

* Please format "none" as a {{constant}} and remove the quotation marks.

Output
* Please change "None" to "none", and format the word as a {{constant}} and remove the quotation marks.

Constraints
* Please add ", all distinct" after "100 integers".

* Please change "100 integers" to "10 integers" because there are at most 4 integers in an array in the cases.

Cases
* Test 2 and Validator 2: Please delete the extra space between 8 and 9.

* Each pair of test and validator should be similar:
  • Please copy the input of Validator 1 to Validator 3, because Validator 3 should be similar to Test 3 instead of being the same.

  • Validator 1: Please revise the case so that "none" is not the output.

  • Validator 2: It should not be the same as Test 2. Please revise it so that it is similar to Test 2.

  • Validator 4: Please include a few negative integers in the input, and some of them should also be part of the output.

Stub generator
* Please remove Lines 6 to 17 because (1) you should not show your solution there, and (2) you should hide the details when you have Reverse mode enabled.

* Please add a write statement, e.g. "write answer".

Thanks.

Thank you very much for your feedback. Sorry for all these mistakes; this is my first contribution. I will do better next time. I have applied the changes. Please take a look and let me know if there is anything else to correct.

Thank you for following up. Just two more points:

Stub generator
* Please delete "INPUT".

Cases
* Please swap Validator 1 with Test 2, so that the output of the first pair of cases contains 2 common elements, and that of the second pair contain 1 only.

Thanks again.

I have applied the modifications.
The thanks go to you!
